Argentinian president Cristina Kirchner has been accused of spending close to £20,000 a day to have the presidential plane bring her the daily newspapers while she was on holiday.

An Argentinian television claims she had the papers flown to the town of Rio Gallegos, in the south Argentinian province of Santa Cruz. 

Footage aired on the programme shows a paper boy leaving the plane in Santa Cruz airport with the newspapers that were then delivered to the president at her house.

