The presenter said: 'We want someone to explain why the president spends so much to get the daily paper about a house when she could read it online the same day or have it delivered in the normal way a day later.'

He added that it would only be acceptable if the president were to pay for it with her own money, but he doubted she was prepared to spend thousands a day just to have the newspapers delivered.

Opposition UCR party politician Anselmo Martinez said: 'I can't say that this is a particular surprise because our country has a history of people using state assets for their own purposes since the time of Nestor Kirchner.

